| New System Detects Calls While Driving                             |
|   from the police-states dept.                                     |
|   posted by CowboyNeal on Saturday June 16, @12:03 (Communications)|
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/16/1457202           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Gary writes "Talking on your cellphone while driving isn't a crime in
most states, but it should be. Studies have shown that people who drive
and talk are many times more likely to have an accident. A new company is
releasing a device to [1]automatically detect drivers talking on their
cell phones. Instead of police officers needing to observe a cellphone in
use, the system automatically detects a cell phone call and records which
car was making the call." The article is fairly light on details, but it
would be interesting to see how the system differentiates from a driver
talking on a cell phone versus a mere passenger.

Discuss this story at:
    http://it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/16/1457202

