| Say Nothing About the Failing Satellite                            |
|   from the or-about-global-warming-either dept.                    |
|   posted by kdawson on Saturday June 16, @14:46 (Space)            |
|   http://politics.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/16/182240      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

The QuikScat satellite used for predicting the intensity and path of
hurricanes could fail at any time (it's already past its designed
lifetime). Without this satellite, the accuracy of US forecasters'
predictions could be degraded by up to 16% — and there are no plans for
any replacement. Bill Proenza, director of the National Hurricane Center,
has been outspokenly critical of his superiors on this situation, but he
has been [0]warned to stop commenting on it.

Discuss this story at:
    http://politics.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/16/182240

Links:
    0. http://www.miamiherald.com/569/story/141782.html


+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| GPLv2 and GPLv3 Coexisting In the Same Project?                    |
|   from the which-side-of-the-fence dept.                           |
|   posted by kdawson on Saturday June 16, @15:43 (GNU is Not Unix)  |
|   http://ask.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/16/1818241          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]cyclop writes "I am coding a data analysis application in my
laboratory that I would like to release as free (as in freedom) software.
Moreover I am going to begin a small OSS game that will be based, in
part, on GPLv2 libraries. Problem is: in both cases, I'd like to be able
to exchange code both with GPLv2 and (future) GPLv3 projects. I have no
particular passions about either license — only thing is I don't want
BSD-style 'do anything you want' licensing but a copyleft license. I know
that [1]GPLv2 and GPLv3 are not compatible. What can I do? Double
licensing? Is there a compatible-with-both license? Adding exceptions?
What do you think is the best way to address the GPLv2-to-GPLv3
transition without ending up on one or the other side of the barricade?"

Discuss this story at:
    http://ask.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/16/1818241

Links:
    0. mailto:devicerandom@gmail.com
    1. http://gplv3.fsf.org/rms-why.html


