[0]pete314 writes "A Vnunet.com article claims that European mobile
operators are [1]unwilling to concede to Apple iPhone partnership demands.
Several operators went as far as to say they 'will never offer the
iPhone.' In the US, Verizon reportedly passed on the device, and AT&T is
rumored to have engaged in a revenue-sharing deal that includes monthly
payments to Cupertino." In Europe, unlike in the US, Apple has the option
of selling the iPhone through its own dealer network without a simlock.

